The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Friday, May 07, 2004 				 School wins neglect plea
 OUR LEGAL REPORTER																								Calcutta High Court on Thursday fined the district inspector of schools, North 24-Parganas, for not sending a representative to the meetings of the managing committee of a school in Ariadaha on political grounds. 																								Justice P.K. Roy ordered the district inspector to pay Rs 1,700 for levelling false allegations against the schools management, and also directed him to nominate a representative within 10 days.																								Elected members of Ariad- aha Sarbamongala Balika Vidyalayas managing committee had complained of a financial crisis as the government grant had been stopped in the absence of a district schools council nominee on the board.
